1
00:02:06,385 --> 00:02:07,944
Do you want to be an actor?

2
00:02:08,024 --> 00:02:11,065
If I play a character written by you,

3
00:02:12,065 --> 00:02:14,065
I'll get to see you more, won't I?

4
00:02:14,665 --> 00:02:15,985
Not to crush your dreams,

5
00:02:16,745 --> 00:02:19,064
but I wouldn't get your hopes up.

6
00:02:19,145 --> 00:02:20,745
Now that I have the opportunity,

7
00:02:22,025 --> 00:02:23,785
I want to give it a shot.

8
00:02:25,344 --> 00:02:27,344
Which one is your dad then?

9
00:02:29,904 --> 00:02:30,985
Who does he think he is

10
00:02:31,064 --> 00:02:33,025
to poke his nose into our business?

11
00:02:33,105 --> 00:02:35,344
Before you lay blame on other people,

12
00:02:35,425 --> 00:02:37,064
why don't you ask yourself

13
00:02:37,665 --> 00:02:38,785
who it is

14
00:02:38,865 --> 00:02:41,145
that's causing her the most distress.

15
00:02:42,785 --> 00:02:44,184
Does that mean--

16
00:02:44,265 --> 00:02:46,865
Na's husband is not Saen.

17
00:02:47,425 --> 00:02:50,665
I only found out later
that he was dating Na.

18
00:02:51,385 --> 00:02:52,865
You think

19
00:02:52,945 --> 00:02:55,505
that I stole Saen from Na, don't you?

20
00:02:56,464 --> 00:02:57,464
I…

21
00:02:58,545 --> 00:02:59,545
Well…

22
00:02:59,624 --> 00:03:01,064
That's okay.

23
00:03:01,145 --> 00:03:02,865
A lot of people think like that.

24
00:03:03,344 --> 00:03:04,705
But the truth is,

25
00:03:05,184 --> 00:03:07,904
it was Na who left Saen.

26
00:03:08,865 --> 00:03:11,145
She chose to marry Sibmeun.

27
00:03:12,344 --> 00:03:13,985
She left him?

28
00:03:14,585 --> 00:03:16,665
She seemed to love him very much.

29
00:03:18,145 --> 00:03:20,665
I think I know why she did it.

30
00:03:21,225 --> 00:03:23,305
She was dealing with many problems

31
00:03:23,385 --> 00:03:25,025
with her house and her grandmother.

32
00:03:25,105 --> 00:03:27,745
Saen was too busy working.

33
00:03:27,825 --> 00:03:30,105
She ended up turning to Sibmeun.

34
00:03:30,184 --> 00:03:32,545
He was a dependable military man.

35
00:03:32,624 --> 00:03:34,464
He was someone she could rely on.

36
00:03:35,025 --> 00:03:38,464
That's how they became close
and got married.

37
00:03:38,545 --> 00:03:41,425
When I married Saen,

38
00:03:41,504 --> 00:03:45,064
Nut was around two years old.

39
00:04:09,265 --> 00:04:12,145
I don't know how to describe
the way I'm feeling.

40
00:04:14,184 --> 00:04:16,985
It's like the world
has suddenly turned upside down.

41
00:04:17,944 --> 00:04:19,425
Bottom becomes top.

42
00:04:19,985 --> 00:04:21,665
Left becomes right.

43
00:04:27,305 --> 00:04:28,505
Like a tree

44
00:04:29,105 --> 00:04:31,225
whose branches grow into the ground,

45
00:04:31,785 --> 00:04:33,225
pointing its roots to the sky.

46
00:04:39,985 --> 00:04:41,065
Like rain

47
00:04:41,745 --> 00:04:43,305
which pours reversely to the sky.

48
00:04:44,065 --> 00:04:47,785
Like a cocoon that turns into a dragonfly.

49
00:04:48,785 --> 00:04:52,745
The human world is different
and more much complicated than my world.

50
00:04:53,385 --> 00:04:57,704
One person's truth might not be another's.

51
00:04:58,704 --> 00:05:02,824
When I was a teddy bear,
I never knew what pain was.

52
00:05:03,545 --> 00:05:05,305
But I know it now.

53
00:05:09,584 --> 00:05:12,065
It is this kind of pain

54
00:05:12,985 --> 00:05:15,584
that makes Mrs. Na wish
to forget the past.

55
00:05:21,704 --> 00:05:23,785
Come eat and take your pills, Grandma.

56
00:05:25,865 --> 00:05:26,865
Grandma!

57
00:05:28,345 --> 00:05:29,345
Grandma!

58
00:05:29,865 --> 00:05:31,385
Grandma.

59
00:05:31,464 --> 00:05:32,905
What's wrong, Na?

60
00:05:32,985 --> 00:05:35,625
I don't know. Please help her, Sibmeun.

61
00:05:41,584 --> 00:05:44,065
Thanks again for your help.

62
00:05:44,785 --> 00:05:47,305
Without you, who knows
what would have happened?

63
00:05:48,024 --> 00:05:49,185
I'm glad I could help.

64
00:05:49,945 --> 00:05:54,225
Luckily, Saen called and told me
he was caught up at work.

65
00:05:54,305 --> 00:05:57,144
He asked me to check
on your grandmother for him,

66
00:05:57,225 --> 00:05:58,584
so I got there in time.

67
00:05:59,665 --> 00:06:00,745
He said

68
00:06:00,824 --> 00:06:03,704
that he wanted to come and see her
once he was finished working,

69
00:06:04,225 --> 00:06:07,144
but he said something else came up.

70
00:06:07,225 --> 00:06:08,665
He may not be able to come.

71
00:06:10,264 --> 00:06:14,105
In that case,
let me buy you dinner to say thank you.

72
00:06:15,545 --> 00:06:16,865
I insist.

73
00:06:26,345 --> 00:06:29,704
This dish is really delicious.
Here are their recommended dishes.

74
00:06:30,625 --> 00:06:33,625
This one is really good.

75
00:06:34,264 --> 00:06:35,264
Right.

76
00:06:39,345 --> 00:06:42,065
Here's what I owe you.
This is the first installment.

77
00:06:43,345 --> 00:06:45,144
I'll pay you back

78
00:06:45,865 --> 00:06:47,505
all the money you loaned me.

79
00:06:47,985 --> 00:06:49,225
You knew?

80
00:06:50,425 --> 00:06:51,945
Who told you?

81
00:06:54,065 --> 00:06:55,785
It doesn't matter who told me.

82
00:06:56,904 --> 00:06:58,785
Just know I won't take advantage of you.

83
00:06:59,425 --> 00:07:01,785
But I wanted you to have this money.

84
00:07:01,865 --> 00:07:03,105
I don't want it back.

85
00:07:03,584 --> 00:07:05,024
But I must repay you.

86
00:07:09,584 --> 00:07:10,865
Thank you…

87
00:07:13,144 --> 00:07:14,425
for the trouble you went to.

88
00:07:16,464 --> 00:07:17,824
You paid my mortgage

89
00:07:18,344 --> 00:07:19,945
and my grandmother's medical bills.

90
00:07:21,065 --> 00:07:23,024
You must be sick of helping me.

91
00:07:24,704 --> 00:07:27,105
You won't have to anymore.

92
00:07:34,545 --> 00:07:36,065
I'm returning this to you.

93
00:07:39,704 --> 00:07:41,225
What do you mean?

94
00:07:47,464 --> 00:07:48,704
It's Sibmeun, isn't it?

95
00:07:53,105 --> 00:07:54,464
It has nothing to do with him.

96
00:07:55,704 --> 00:07:57,545
I made this decision on my own.

97
00:08:00,784 --> 00:08:03,584
The other night,
Grandma's condition got worse.

98
00:08:05,945 --> 00:08:08,945
Sibmeun promised her
he would take care of me.

99
00:08:10,584 --> 00:08:12,904
And I think it makes sense.

100
00:08:14,065 --> 00:08:16,545
We're getting married,
so Grandma won't have to worry.

101
00:08:24,185 --> 00:08:25,464
Here he is.

102
00:08:29,625 --> 00:08:30,665
Please excuse me.

103
00:08:31,144 --> 00:08:32,264
Bye.

104
00:08:57,785 --> 00:09:01,825
Whether you are separated
in life or by death, the pain is the same.

105
00:09:05,905 --> 00:09:08,905
It's because of this torture and pain

106
00:09:10,064 --> 00:09:11,705
that humans choose to forget.

107
00:09:21,944 --> 00:09:24,544
-Where are you?
-Mrs. Na.

108
00:09:27,665 --> 00:09:30,345
When you face
the worst kind of grief like that,

109
00:09:31,265 --> 00:09:33,505
the only way to survive

110
00:09:33,585 --> 00:09:37,304
is to forget and create a new reality.

111
00:09:45,825 --> 00:09:49,905
One where you won't get hurt
or be upset ever again.

112
00:10:07,985 --> 00:10:09,184
Don't worry.

113
00:10:12,785 --> 00:10:14,424
Thank you, both of you,

114
00:10:15,025 --> 00:10:17,025
for convincing Mom to go see a doctor.

115
00:10:18,345 --> 00:10:21,385
Na isn't a stranger to us.
We're happy to help.

116
00:10:26,745 --> 00:10:29,304
I didn't know that she had stopped
taking her medication.

117
00:10:30,465 --> 00:10:31,785
She always goes by herself

118
00:10:32,345 --> 00:10:33,665
for her appointments.

119
00:10:35,465 --> 00:10:37,265
But she lied to the doctor.

120
00:10:39,105 --> 00:10:41,105
Don't blame yourself.

121
00:10:43,225 --> 00:10:44,705
Now that you know about it,

122
00:10:45,505 --> 00:10:49,665
you can take better care of your mom.

123
00:10:50,985 --> 00:10:53,705
And her condition isn't as bad
as it was before.

124
00:10:54,265 --> 00:10:56,025
I think that's a good sign.

125
00:11:00,505 --> 00:11:02,465
But I still don't get it.

126
00:11:02,544 --> 00:11:04,705
Why won't Mom accept the truth?

127
00:11:05,985 --> 00:11:10,304
Some truths are not easy to accept,

128
00:11:11,785 --> 00:11:15,385
especially the ones that left scars.

129
00:11:17,025 --> 00:11:19,225
You want to bury them as deep as possible.

130
00:11:22,625 --> 00:11:25,585
Those who are strong can handle the truth.

131
00:11:26,064 --> 00:11:27,265
It doesn't affect them.

132
00:11:28,465 --> 00:11:29,944
But for some people,

133
00:11:30,785 --> 00:11:32,465
it's just too much to bear.

134
00:11:36,824 --> 00:11:38,785
In order to accept the truth,

135
00:11:39,705 --> 00:11:43,865
you must first accept
that you have been scarred.

136
00:11:48,304 --> 00:11:52,064
Your mom may have some scars

137
00:11:52,944 --> 00:11:54,865
that she can't bear to face right now.

138
00:11:56,064 --> 00:11:57,625
You've got to give her time.

139
00:11:59,585 --> 00:12:01,985
Give her some time, Nut.

140
00:12:03,105 --> 00:12:04,064
Hang in there.

141
00:12:07,184 --> 00:12:09,225
-Mom.
-Na.

142
00:12:09,304 --> 00:12:10,304
Na.

143
00:12:12,944 --> 00:12:15,465
Come to our house sometime, Nut.

144
00:12:15,544 --> 00:12:17,785
Bring your mom with you
for a change of pace.

145
00:12:18,265 --> 00:12:20,785
I'll cook you guys something nice.

146
00:12:23,424 --> 00:12:25,785
I'll take your offer for that.

147
00:12:25,865 --> 00:12:28,345
Don't bail on us,
or I'll have to eat everything.

148
00:12:29,304 --> 00:12:31,184
I'll take my mom home, then.

149
00:12:32,705 --> 00:12:33,865
Thank you.

150
00:12:45,625 --> 00:12:46,625
Na.

151
00:12:53,064 --> 00:12:54,064
Excuse me.

152
00:12:54,544 --> 00:12:55,625
Mr. Saen?

153
00:13:00,145 --> 00:13:02,304
-You are…
-I'm Sitha.

154
00:13:12,745 --> 00:13:13,785
Have some coffee.

155
00:13:16,345 --> 00:13:17,385
Thank you.

156
00:13:18,745 --> 00:13:20,985
Long time no see.

157
00:13:21,064 --> 00:13:24,385
It must be eight or nine years
since Sibmeun passed away.

158
00:13:25,665 --> 00:13:28,785
I don't come around this way very often.
Just once in a while.

159
00:13:29,704 --> 00:13:30,944
I had some business today.

160
00:13:32,665 --> 00:13:34,025
I just saw Nut and Na.

161
00:13:35,025 --> 00:13:36,265
Is Na sick?

162
00:13:36,824 --> 00:13:39,105
Well, it's her old condition.

163
00:13:42,944 --> 00:13:44,345
It has come back?

164
00:13:44,985 --> 00:13:47,704
I've heard she got better.

165
00:13:48,704 --> 00:13:50,985
She is better, but she's still sick.

166
00:13:51,064 --> 00:13:53,824
Nut just found out
that she stopped taking her pills,

167
00:13:53,905 --> 00:13:55,465
so her condition got worse.

168
00:13:57,665 --> 00:14:01,225
But she's seeing a doctor now.
That should help.

169
00:14:02,265 --> 00:14:04,265
Nut found someone to look after her.

170
00:14:05,985 --> 00:14:09,745
If you're worried about her,
go visit her sometime.

171
00:14:09,824 --> 00:14:11,745
She would be happy to see you.

172
00:15:01,025 --> 00:15:02,025
Are you hungry, Mom?

173
00:15:02,785 --> 00:15:04,064
I'll order you something.

174
00:15:04,544 --> 00:15:06,064
You can eat and take your pills.

175
00:15:38,704 --> 00:15:39,584
Mom.

176
00:15:41,105 --> 00:15:42,345
I have to get back to work.

177
00:15:43,785 --> 00:15:45,424
Call me if you need anything.

178
00:15:56,505 --> 00:15:57,865
Your mom

179
00:15:58,464 --> 00:16:00,985
may have some scars

180
00:16:01,625 --> 00:16:03,785
that she can't bear to face right now.

181
00:16:04,265 --> 00:16:06,025
Give her some time, Nut.

182
00:16:07,985 --> 00:16:10,105
Have you told Nut about this?

183
00:16:11,064 --> 00:16:12,665
He wouldn't want to hear it.

184
00:16:12,745 --> 00:16:15,985
You know when I talk about Saen,

185
00:16:17,385 --> 00:16:19,184
Nut always gets angry.

186
00:16:21,265 --> 00:16:25,145
I wonder if he's angry
because he doesn't believe me…

187
00:16:27,064 --> 00:16:30,025
or that he doesn't like me.

188
00:16:34,225 --> 00:16:36,584
Everything I do seems to be wrong.

189
00:16:41,064 --> 00:16:42,064
Mom.

190
00:16:43,785 --> 00:16:44,785
I'm sorry…

191
00:17:24,424 --> 00:17:26,585
Although she isn't ready
to see the picture,

192
00:17:27,825 --> 00:17:29,665
I still think you should keep it.

193
00:17:31,185 --> 00:17:32,905
She might want to see it someday.

194
00:17:48,385 --> 00:17:49,825
Before you worry about me,

195
00:17:53,105 --> 00:17:54,425
worry about yourself first.

196
00:18:40,024 --> 00:18:41,305
I know what happened

197
00:18:42,625 --> 00:18:44,625
between your mom and Mr. Saen.

198
00:18:45,665 --> 00:18:47,145
Jan told me everything.

199
00:18:49,105 --> 00:18:50,385
Didn't I tell you

200
00:18:51,465 --> 00:18:55,385
not to talk to her
as long as you're living here?

201
00:18:58,024 --> 00:18:59,225
I know that.

202
00:19:00,345 --> 00:19:02,905
But she's telling the truth, isn't she?

203
00:19:04,024 --> 00:19:06,065
Your mom has the wrong idea about Saen.

204
00:19:06,545 --> 00:19:08,945
That's why you try to make her forget him.

205
00:19:12,545 --> 00:19:14,185
But I can't do it.

206
00:19:16,625 --> 00:19:19,024
Now, my mom is in love
with someone else's husband.

207
00:19:22,905 --> 00:19:24,225
It's too bad.

208
00:19:25,105 --> 00:19:27,105
You know about it,
but you can't do anything.

209
00:19:28,264 --> 00:19:29,984
That's worse than not knowing.

210
00:19:32,825 --> 00:19:35,425
You must have been shocked
when you found out.

211
00:19:37,465 --> 00:19:40,585
I was so shocked
that I didn't know what to say.

212
00:19:43,784 --> 00:19:45,504
I don't know what to do about it.

213
00:19:52,625 --> 00:19:53,945
I'm sorry.

214
00:19:58,545 --> 00:19:59,784
What for?

215
00:20:02,984 --> 00:20:05,705
I've always thought
that you were mean to your mom.

216
00:20:07,825 --> 00:20:10,024
But she was mean to you too,

217
00:20:11,705 --> 00:20:13,665
even if she didn't mean it.

218
00:20:18,545 --> 00:20:20,385
I'm sorry too.

219
00:20:21,065 --> 00:20:22,145
Why?

220
00:20:23,784 --> 00:20:24,984
I hurt you,

221
00:20:26,225 --> 00:20:27,705
though you did nothing wrong.

222
00:20:29,705 --> 00:20:31,385
You just didn't know.

223
00:20:36,065 --> 00:20:39,305
Everyone who comes near me gets hurt.

224
00:20:43,105 --> 00:20:44,345
It's all right.

225
00:20:44,945 --> 00:20:47,305
I wasn't hurt or angry with you.

226
00:20:48,385 --> 00:20:50,385
I know how much pain you're in.

227
00:20:51,465 --> 00:20:54,065
It must be a hundred times
worse than this wound.

228
00:20:57,264 --> 00:20:59,425
How come you get me,
even with your amnesia?

229
00:21:01,385 --> 00:21:03,744
Even my friends and family don't get me.

230
00:21:50,744 --> 00:21:52,305
It's all right, Nut.

231
00:21:56,504 --> 00:21:58,744
Even if the world doesn't get you,

232
00:22:01,024 --> 00:22:03,145
I'll always try to understand you.

233
00:22:05,465 --> 00:22:07,305
I will be here for you.

234
00:22:34,665 --> 00:22:36,744
You don't have to be strong all the time.

235
00:22:39,305 --> 00:22:40,625
Don't fake a smile

236
00:22:41,825 --> 00:22:43,585
when you want to cry.

237
00:22:46,145 --> 00:22:49,744
When you're sad,
don't think that no one is there for you.

238
00:22:50,905 --> 00:22:52,945
Although that teddy bear is gone,

239
00:22:54,705 --> 00:22:56,385
you still have me.

240
00:22:59,264 --> 00:23:01,984
I will hold you in its place.

241
00:23:44,465 --> 00:23:47,504
Horrible things happened
to Nut and his mom yesterday,

242
00:23:48,585 --> 00:23:51,865
but at least something good came of it.

243
00:24:01,345 --> 00:24:02,665
Hang on.

244
00:24:02,744 --> 00:24:05,145
It's not what Jan and Nhong
always gossip about.

245
00:24:08,465 --> 00:24:10,264
The good thing that happened

246
00:24:10,865 --> 00:24:12,625
is I got to hug Nut last night,

247
00:24:13,385 --> 00:24:15,024
and he hugged me back.

248
00:24:20,585 --> 00:24:22,825
I hope it cheered him up a little.

249
00:24:23,744 --> 00:24:26,705
That would make me so happy.

250
00:24:31,185 --> 00:24:32,665
Why am I thinking about him?

251
00:24:33,544 --> 00:24:34,784
I'm going crazy.

252
00:24:52,825 --> 00:24:54,504
Come on, son.

253
00:24:55,705 --> 00:24:58,225
Here's some hot shrimp porridge.

254
00:24:59,225 --> 00:25:01,024
Wow.

255
00:25:01,585 --> 00:25:03,185
It looks great, Dad.

256
00:25:03,264 --> 00:25:05,705
Eat up, then. Isn't it your favorite?

257
00:25:06,264 --> 00:25:08,065
It was Neung's favorite.

258
00:25:11,264 --> 00:25:12,544
But…

259
00:25:12,625 --> 00:25:14,385
But I like it too.

260
00:25:14,465 --> 00:25:17,905
If Neung was still here,
there wouldn't be any left for me.

261
00:25:19,945 --> 00:25:22,544
It has been ten years now.

262
00:25:23,225 --> 00:25:24,665
Time flies.

263
00:25:25,225 --> 00:25:27,744
Dad, let's go make merit for Neung.

264
00:25:31,345 --> 00:25:34,585
Sure, choose where we'll do it.

265
00:25:34,665 --> 00:25:36,825
I already have an idea.

266
00:25:37,385 --> 00:25:38,345
What is it?

267
00:25:38,905 --> 00:25:41,425
I want to donate some sports equipment

268
00:25:41,504 --> 00:25:43,544
to a school that needs it.

269
00:25:43,625 --> 00:25:45,825
Neung loved basketball.

270
00:25:45,905 --> 00:25:48,665
