397
00:36:57,464 --> 00:36:59,345
Nut likes to read.

398
00:36:59,424 --> 00:37:01,145
He likes to read everything.

399
00:37:01,705 --> 00:37:05,384
He likes poems, novels,
history, and travel guides.

400
00:37:05,464 --> 00:37:07,225
He also likes picture books.

401
00:37:07,305 --> 00:37:09,265
I remember there's one book
he really likes.

402
00:37:10,145 --> 00:37:11,705
He once told me

403
00:37:12,265 --> 00:37:14,185
that besides reading books,

404
00:37:14,265 --> 00:37:16,384
you can also read people who read books.

405
00:37:17,025 --> 00:37:19,985
That's cool. It sounds like something
a writer would say.

406
00:37:20,065 --> 00:37:22,625
What else does he like, other than books?

407
00:37:23,944 --> 00:37:25,065
Well…

408
00:37:26,065 --> 00:37:28,665
He likes to watch TV series.

409
00:37:28,745 --> 00:37:31,225
He enjoys watching everything.

410
00:37:31,305 --> 00:37:33,944
He can stay up all night
watching something he likes.

411
00:37:34,625 --> 00:37:36,785
Sometimes he even forgets about his mom.

412
00:37:37,345 --> 00:37:38,985
I see.

413
00:37:39,065 --> 00:37:43,065
That's why he never replies
to my late-night texts.

414
00:37:44,585 --> 00:37:46,025
And things he doesn't like?

415
00:37:47,185 --> 00:37:49,025
He doesn't like vegetables.

416
00:37:51,225 --> 00:37:53,384
He doesn't like anyone
going into his room.

417
00:37:55,185 --> 00:37:57,025
He doesn't like the lady next door.

418
00:38:00,424 --> 00:38:01,464
And…

419
00:38:02,745 --> 00:38:04,904
