540
00:45:31,984 --> 00:45:33,665
I want everything ready. Go.

541
00:45:33,745 --> 00:45:34,904
Let's go.

542
00:45:34,984 --> 00:45:36,345
-Juea, no.
-Knock it off.

543
00:45:36,424 --> 00:45:38,705
-No, Juea.
-Stop it.

544
00:45:38,785 --> 00:45:40,265
-Juea, please.
-Calm down, Gen.

545
00:45:40,345 --> 00:45:42,105
Gen, calm down.

546
00:45:42,185 --> 00:45:44,705
You should keep work
and your private life separate.

547
00:45:44,785 --> 00:45:46,424
Keep that in mind.

548
00:45:46,505 --> 00:45:48,065
Can you even do that, Pribpree?

549
00:45:48,145 --> 00:45:49,384
Sure, I can.

550
00:45:54,464 --> 00:45:56,864
Honey, can you hand me the shovel?

551
00:46:00,904 --> 00:46:02,225
Thank you.

552
00:46:11,265 --> 00:46:12,505
Okay.

553
00:46:14,025 --> 00:46:14,984
Isn't it pretty?

554
00:46:17,305 --> 00:46:19,505
It's like the one
in my grandmother's house.

555
00:46:23,585 --> 00:46:24,705
Honey.

556
00:46:25,665 --> 00:46:27,745
Where should I put this?

557
00:46:44,825 --> 00:46:46,145
Honey!

558
00:46:46,225 --> 00:46:48,065
Honey!

559
00:46:48,145 --> 00:46:50,185
Mrs. Na, what's wrong?

560
00:46:50,265 --> 00:46:51,745
Little Prince.

561
00:46:51,825 --> 00:46:53,424
I can't find Saen.

562
00:46:54,265 --> 00:46:55,944
Did you see him?

563
00:46:56,025 --> 00:46:57,464
Did he say where he went?

564
00:46:59,545 --> 00:47:00,785
Do you know where he is?

565
00:47:00,864 --> 00:47:02,464
If Mom takes her medication,

566
00:47:02,545 --> 00:47:05,065
the doctor said
she will gradually stop hallucinating.

567
00:47:07,185 --> 00:47:08,745
She might be frightened sometimes.

568
00:47:11,065 --> 00:47:12,625
Please look after her for me.

569
00:47:15,585 --> 00:47:17,305
If she mentions my dad,

570
00:47:18,025 --> 00:47:19,665
just listen to her

571
00:47:20,345 --> 00:47:21,665
and then change the subject.

572
00:47:23,305 --> 00:47:24,705
Take her mind off him.

573
00:47:26,545 --> 00:47:28,105
I haven't seen him.

574
00:47:33,185 --> 00:47:36,225
It's almost noon. No wonder I'm so hungry.

575
00:47:36,305 --> 00:47:39,065
Can you make me something delicious?

576
00:47:40,105 --> 00:47:41,625
Is that the time?

577
00:47:42,464 --> 00:47:45,265
-I'll see what we have in the fridge.
-Okay.

578
00:48:06,265 --> 00:48:08,305
Next one.

579
00:48:08,384 --> 00:48:09,384
Good job.

580
00:48:10,505 --> 00:48:11,505
Hey…

581
00:48:11,984 --> 00:48:14,265
Song, are you good at basketball?

582
00:48:14,345 --> 00:48:17,345
-I'm pretty good.
-Okay.

583
00:48:18,545 --> 00:48:21,345
Give the script a read.
We'll continue next week.

584
00:48:21,424 --> 00:48:23,265
-Okay.
-Listen.

585
00:48:23,345 --> 00:48:25,745
Study the script.
Immerse yourself in the character.

586
00:48:25,825 --> 00:48:28,864
Also, you need to work on your skills.

587
00:48:28,944 --> 00:48:31,065
You've got to look cool
while you're dribbling.

588
00:48:31,145 --> 00:48:32,345
It will be awesome.

589
00:48:32,424 --> 00:48:34,625
-Okay.
-Show me what you can do.

590
00:48:34,705 --> 00:48:36,105
Thank you, guys.

591
00:48:36,185 --> 00:48:39,545
I'll go get changed and take off, then.

592
00:48:39,625 --> 00:48:42,585
-Goodbye.
-Thank you for today.

593
00:48:43,265 --> 00:48:44,145
Goodbye.

594
00:48:48,025 --> 00:48:49,625
I'll borrow your partner to train.

595
00:48:54,305 --> 00:48:55,345
What partner?

596
00:48:56,944 --> 00:48:58,225
Did he mean my wife?

597
00:49:04,145 --> 00:49:05,345
Do you miss Neung?

598
00:49:05,864 --> 00:49:07,505
I think of him all the time.

599
00:49:08,105 --> 00:49:09,625
He passed away so suddenly.

600
00:49:10,545 --> 00:49:12,145
Who would have known

601
00:49:13,065 --> 00:49:14,904
that I would never get to hug him again?

602
00:49:24,384 --> 00:49:26,625
Why did you love him so much?

603
00:49:27,145 --> 00:49:30,864
Is it because he was always there for you
to help you with things?

604
00:49:33,265 --> 00:49:36,065
Love is not about just being around

605
00:49:36,145 --> 00:49:38,665
or doing things for your partner.

606
00:49:41,145 --> 00:49:42,984
When you love someone,

607
00:49:44,585 --> 00:49:47,864
you do things for them
because you care about them.

608
00:49:49,424 --> 00:49:51,705
Saen has always cared for me.

609
00:50:02,225 --> 00:50:04,065
You're just like him, Little Prince.

610
00:50:05,825 --> 00:50:08,345
You really care for me.

611
00:50:10,025 --> 00:50:11,305
Thank you.

612
00:50:13,225 --> 00:50:15,025
Someone else cares about you.

613
00:50:15,705 --> 00:50:17,984
He may not always be around,

614
00:50:18,464 --> 00:50:20,225
but he always cares about you.

615
00:50:21,185 --> 00:50:22,424
Who's that?

616
00:50:23,145 --> 00:50:24,504
Nut.

617
00:50:27,065 --> 00:50:29,145
He might not show it,

618
00:50:30,625 --> 00:50:32,345
but he loves you very much.

619
00:50:33,864 --> 00:50:37,345
He always looks after you when you sleep.

620
00:50:57,065 --> 00:51:00,665
When he hears you scream,
he's the first one to run and see you.

621
00:51:02,585 --> 00:51:04,265
When you cry,

622
00:51:04,785 --> 00:51:06,785
he secretly cries with you.

623
00:51:08,464 --> 00:51:10,745
When you smile,

624
00:51:10,825 --> 00:51:12,984
I think it makes him smile too.

625
00:51:14,025 --> 00:51:16,384
That's not right.

626
00:51:18,545 --> 00:51:20,145
You only need one.

627
00:51:33,984 --> 00:51:35,185
Mrs. Na.

628
00:51:36,185 --> 00:51:38,984
It's good to think about someone

629
00:51:39,745 --> 00:51:41,065
who's far away.

630
00:51:42,585 --> 00:51:44,665
But you should also think of those

631
00:51:45,384 --> 00:51:47,384
who are close by.

632
00:51:49,585 --> 00:51:50,665
If someone is far away,

633
00:51:51,145 --> 00:51:53,225
all you can do is think about them.

634
00:51:54,545 --> 00:51:56,424
It's those who are close by

635
00:51:56,504 --> 00:51:58,384
that you can do things for.

636
00:52:11,305 --> 00:52:12,825
It's time to take your medicine.

637
00:52:22,984 --> 00:52:24,265
Who's at the door?

638
00:52:24,745 --> 00:52:25,825
I'll go check.

639
00:52:49,545 --> 00:52:50,665
Song.

640
00:52:51,305 --> 00:52:52,545
Who is it, Tofu?

641
00:52:54,145 --> 00:52:56,185
-Hello, Mrs. Na.
-Hello.

642
00:52:56,265 --> 00:52:57,464
This is Song.

643
00:52:57,545 --> 00:53:00,065
He's Neung's brother.
Neung was at school with Nut.

644
00:53:00,545 --> 00:53:02,705
Are you here to see Nut?

645
00:53:03,185 --> 00:53:05,585
No, I came to see Tofu.

646
00:53:08,145 --> 00:53:09,864
Are you busy? I need your help.

647
00:53:23,904 --> 00:53:25,705
You said you've never played before.

648
00:53:26,984 --> 00:53:29,025
I don't remember playing before.

649
00:53:29,105 --> 00:53:30,545
My hands moved on their own.

650
00:53:31,345 --> 00:53:32,745
You're quite good.

651
00:53:35,785 --> 00:53:37,025
Let me ask you something.

652
00:53:37,585 --> 00:53:38,545
Sure.

653
00:53:39,145 --> 00:53:41,785
Did Neung ever buy
a teddy bear for anyone?

654
00:53:45,705 --> 00:53:47,864
Neung's girlfriend
didn't like teddy bears.

655
00:53:47,944 --> 00:53:49,585
She liked flowers.

656
00:53:50,745 --> 00:53:52,065
Flowers?

657
00:53:53,504 --> 00:53:55,705
Nut doesn't like flowers.

658
00:53:57,065 --> 00:53:57,904
Nut?

659
00:53:59,665 --> 00:54:01,265
Do you mean Donut?

660
00:54:02,105 --> 00:54:05,105
No. Neung's girlfriend was Nhing.

661
00:54:05,185 --> 00:54:07,065
She's Donut's best friend.

662
00:54:08,225 --> 00:54:09,464
Nhing was really pretty.

663
00:54:10,424 --> 00:54:12,145
-Nhing?
-Yes.

664
00:54:14,345 --> 00:54:17,785
I can't really remember
what she looked like.

665
00:54:18,345 --> 00:54:20,105
I only remember that she was gorgeous.

666
00:54:20,825 --> 00:54:22,984
I was in second grade back then.

667
00:54:24,025 --> 00:54:25,625
If you want to know more,

668
00:54:28,864 --> 00:54:30,464
you'll have to ask my dad.

669
00:54:36,225 --> 00:54:37,504
Let's play some more.

670
00:56:44,265 --> 00:56:47,025
This is Tofu, a friend of mine.

671
00:56:52,225 --> 00:56:53,345
You look just like him.

672
00:56:58,825 --> 00:56:59,825
Hello.

673
00:57:06,145 --> 00:57:07,024
Dad.

674
00:57:08,705 --> 00:57:10,105
Come on. Let's play.

675
00:57:12,504 --> 00:57:13,504
-Here.
-Okay.

676
00:57:19,825 --> 00:57:22,265
Come on.

677
00:57:27,825 --> 00:57:29,305
Bring it on.

678
00:57:57,145 --> 00:57:58,384
Are you tired, Dad?

679
00:57:59,185 --> 00:58:00,904
I'm a police officer.

680
00:58:00,984 --> 00:58:02,625
-This is nothing.
-No.

681
00:58:03,185 --> 00:58:05,024
I mean are you tired from smiling?

682
00:58:05,105 --> 00:58:08,625
You son of a gun. Are you teasing me?

683
00:58:10,305 --> 00:58:12,825
It has been a while
since I heard you laugh this loudly.

684
00:58:12,904 --> 00:58:15,585
Gosh. Are you mocking me?

685
00:58:15,665 --> 00:58:19,745
I'll teach you a lesson.

686
00:58:33,904 --> 00:58:35,585
-Mom.
-Yes?

687
00:58:35,665 --> 00:58:38,024
-Where's Tofu?
-He went to his friend's house.

688
00:58:39,545 --> 00:58:41,225
-His friend?
-Yes.

689
00:58:41,305 --> 00:58:42,345
What friend?

690
00:58:42,825 --> 00:58:44,825
His name is Song.

691
00:58:44,904 --> 00:58:47,305
He asked Tofu to play basketball with him.

692
00:58:48,585 --> 00:58:50,345
Tofu said he would text you.

693
00:58:57,705 --> 00:59:00,065
Don't bother if it's too much trouble.

694
00:59:01,024 --> 00:59:01,864
What was that?

695
00:59:03,345 --> 00:59:04,345
It's nothing.

696
00:59:05,464 --> 00:59:07,825
Take a shower and then come eat.

697
00:59:08,504 --> 00:59:09,625
Okay.

698
00:59:23,785 --> 00:59:25,185
The bulb is gone again.

699
00:59:25,745 --> 00:59:27,305
Come on.

700
00:59:27,384 --> 00:59:29,105
Go on, shoot!

701
00:59:29,185 --> 00:59:30,024
Hey!

702
00:59:30,105 --> 00:59:31,065
-Yes!
-Oh, wow!

703
00:59:31,145 --> 00:59:32,785
Wow!

704
00:59:40,265 --> 00:59:41,705
You're good.

705
00:59:41,785 --> 00:59:44,265
You don't look sick
like Song told me you were.

706
00:59:45,545 --> 00:59:47,305
I just do what Song taught me.

707
00:59:49,904 --> 00:59:53,705
Tofu, don't you want
to ask my dad something? Go on.

708
00:59:55,065 --> 00:59:56,105
What is it?

709
00:59:56,585 --> 01:00:00,665
Tofu wants to know
about Neung's girlfriend.

710
01:00:05,424 --> 01:00:09,145
You see, Tofu's living with Nut.

711
01:00:09,825 --> 01:00:13,024
He's the screenwriter
for the series I'm going to be in.

712
01:00:13,105 --> 01:00:15,825
He was also Neung's junior at school.

713
01:00:16,545 --> 01:00:19,345
I know Tofu through Nut.

714
01:00:20,424 --> 01:00:23,265
Tofu probably wants to know
about Neung's girlfriend,

715
01:00:23,345 --> 01:00:24,904
so he knows how to act

716
01:00:25,904 --> 01:00:28,345
in case they meet each other.

717
01:00:28,424 --> 01:00:30,065
Is that right, Tofu?

718
01:00:32,225 --> 01:00:33,504
That's right.

719
01:00:36,024 --> 01:00:38,424
I met Neung's girlfriend
a couple of times.

720
01:00:38,944 --> 01:00:40,225
She was quite sweet.

721
01:00:41,185 --> 01:00:44,185
She was chatty,
and she was a good influence on him.

722
01:00:44,265 --> 01:00:46,225
They got into the same college.

723
01:00:47,424 --> 01:00:50,585
I was hoping they could help each other
study in college.

724
01:00:51,384 --> 01:00:52,384
It's too bad

725
01:00:53,504 --> 01:00:55,185
that Neung had an accident.

726
01:00:59,065 --> 01:01:00,785
Other than his girlfriend,

727
01:01:01,305 --> 01:01:04,345
did Neung ever bring anyone else here?

728
01:01:05,665 --> 01:01:06,984
Just his friends.

729
01:01:07,464 --> 01:01:09,464
They're all grown up now.

730
01:01:11,545 --> 01:01:14,745
But he never brought
any of his juniors home.

731
01:01:15,464 --> 01:01:16,745
Not even Nut?

732
01:01:18,545 --> 01:01:20,185
He's the guy I just told you about.

733
01:01:20,745 --> 01:01:21,825
I see.

734
01:01:22,504 --> 01:01:24,424
I've never heard of Nut before.

735
01:01:25,504 --> 01:01:28,185
And Neung never mentioned him.

736
01:01:30,024 --> 01:01:31,225
How is that possible?

737
01:01:32,185 --> 01:01:35,464
Neung was the most important person
in Nut's life.

738
01:01:37,785 --> 01:01:40,265
But to him, Nut didn't exist at all.

739
01:01:42,984 --> 01:01:44,464
Could it be

740
01:01:45,225 --> 01:01:48,105
that Neung wasn't the one
who brought me to life?

741
01:01:58,265 --> 01:01:59,265
Tofu.

742
01:02:00,225 --> 01:02:01,225
Tofu.

743
01:02:02,384 --> 01:02:03,545
We're here.

744
01:02:06,464 --> 01:02:07,305
Right.

745
01:02:12,305 --> 01:02:13,305
Thank you.

746
01:02:15,545 --> 01:02:18,024
Please tell your dad that I'm sorry

747
01:02:18,625 --> 01:02:20,665
if I asked anything inappropriate.

748
01:02:21,305 --> 01:02:22,904
He was actually glad to see you.

749
01:02:23,585 --> 01:02:25,265
You should come by again.

750
01:02:25,825 --> 01:02:29,065
My dad would be thrilled
to see your face more often.

751
01:02:34,265 --> 01:02:37,345
Why is the front gate open like that?

752
01:02:37,424 --> 01:02:39,145
Isn't Mrs. Na home alone?

753
01:02:40,225 --> 01:02:42,105
It's very dangerous.

754
01:02:42,185 --> 01:02:44,185
You don't know who might pass by.

755
01:03:32,904 --> 01:03:33,745
No.

756
01:03:33,825 --> 01:03:35,024
Be careful!

757
01:04:15,145 --> 01:04:16,265
Saen.

758
01:04:18,864 --> 01:04:19,864
Na.

759
01:04:29,585 --> 01:04:31,305
It's really you, Saen.

760
01:04:50,145 --> 01:04:51,185
It's me.

761
01:05:08,024 --> 01:05:09,185
I have to go.

762
01:05:10,745 --> 01:05:12,024
Where are you going?

763
01:05:15,265 --> 01:05:16,265
Hey, kid.

764
01:05:17,984 --> 01:05:19,065
Take care of her.

765
01:05:19,785 --> 01:05:20,825
I will.

766
01:05:22,504 --> 01:05:23,504
Wait.

767
01:05:28,864 --> 01:05:31,185
-Where are you going, Saen?
-Mrs. Na.

768
01:05:35,105 --> 01:05:37,625
Please go after him.

769
01:05:38,305 --> 01:05:40,265
Where is he going this late at night?

770
01:05:43,984 --> 01:05:45,625
I'm sure he'll be back soon.

771
01:05:46,585 --> 01:05:48,345
You should go inside.

772
01:05:48,424 --> 01:05:50,305
Nut will be angry if he sees you outside.

773
01:06:04,825 --> 01:06:06,785
Weren't you going to come see your wife?

774
01:06:20,904 --> 01:06:22,065
Come sit down.

775
01:06:28,864 --> 01:06:30,345
Are you hurt?

776
01:06:32,464 --> 01:06:33,504
I'm fine.

777
01:06:34,464 --> 01:06:36,305
Can you go after Saen?

778
01:06:37,424 --> 01:06:38,585
Please.

779
01:06:41,145 --> 01:06:43,225
Please go after him.

780
01:06:43,305 --> 01:06:44,384
All right.

781
01:06:44,464 --> 01:06:45,864
What's wrong, Mom?

782
01:06:47,705 --> 01:06:49,864
I heard you scream.

783
01:06:52,265 --> 01:06:53,825
She fell off a ladder.

784
01:06:55,225 --> 01:06:56,745
Why would you climb a ladder?

785
01:06:56,825 --> 01:07:00,864
The lightbulb burned out.
I thought I could change it, but I fell.

786
01:07:01,625 --> 01:07:02,944
Why didn't you ask me?

787
01:07:03,024 --> 01:07:05,065
You were in your room.

788
01:07:05,145 --> 01:07:06,625
I didn't want to disturb you.

789
01:07:08,105 --> 01:07:09,105
As for you, you jerk.

790
01:07:10,065 --> 01:07:11,665
You were busy flirting outside.

791
01:07:13,105 --> 01:07:14,864
Don't tell him off.

792
01:07:16,024 --> 01:07:18,464
And don't call him that.

793
01:07:19,504 --> 01:07:21,105
What should I call him?

794
01:07:22,024 --> 01:07:23,904
Baby brother Tofu?

795
01:07:26,504 --> 01:07:27,825
That's cute, actually.

796
01:07:34,424 --> 01:07:35,944
Sweet baby brother Tofu.

797
01:07:36,785 --> 01:07:38,065
Has your ass…

798
01:07:39,024 --> 01:07:40,384
Have you eaten yet?

799
01:07:41,225 --> 01:07:42,225
No.

800
01:07:43,305 --> 01:07:44,904
Please cook something for him.

801
01:07:45,785 --> 01:07:48,225
You little shit… I mean…

802
01:07:48,305 --> 01:07:49,705
my dear Tofu.

803
01:07:50,185 --> 01:07:51,544
Help me change the lightbulb.

804
01:07:51,625 --> 01:07:52,864
Let's go.

805
01:08:02,424 --> 01:08:04,544
Please don't be mad at your mom.

806
01:08:05,024 --> 01:08:07,065
It was my fault for leaving her alone.

807
01:08:07,705 --> 01:08:09,984
I thought I wouldn't be gone too long,

808
01:08:10,504 --> 01:08:13,745
but I got carried away
chatting with Mr. Anik and Song.

809
01:08:15,345 --> 01:08:16,345
Mr. Anik?

810
01:08:16,825 --> 01:08:18,145
He's Song's dad.

811
01:08:19,065 --> 01:08:21,584
When he first saw me, he was shocked.

812
01:08:22,065 --> 01:08:23,704
Just like Song was.

813
01:08:25,784 --> 01:08:26,945
Anyway,

814
01:08:27,025 --> 01:08:28,584
aren't you curious

815
01:08:29,105 --> 01:08:31,865
why I look exactly like Neung?

816
01:08:42,504 --> 01:08:44,065
If I weren't,

817
01:08:44,664 --> 01:08:46,225
I wouldn't have let you live here

818
01:08:47,384 --> 01:08:48,784
or taken you to Neung's house.

819
01:08:52,424 --> 01:08:54,704
I used to think
that you might be a relative,

820
01:08:55,265 --> 01:08:56,265
even a sibling.

821
01:08:56,744 --> 01:08:58,544
But Neung's father doesn't know you.

822
01:08:59,504 --> 01:09:01,345
So, you're not their family.

823
01:09:09,584 --> 01:09:11,504
Now that you know
I'm not related to Neung,

824
01:09:12,544 --> 01:09:14,544
you won't kick me out, will you?

825
01:09:16,664 --> 01:09:18,145
If I wanted to,

826
01:09:18,624 --> 01:09:20,825
I would've left you
at the temple that day.

827
01:09:21,825 --> 01:09:22,905
Gosh.

828
01:09:23,464 --> 01:09:25,424
I'm a bear, not a dog.

829
01:09:27,025 --> 01:09:28,305
What did you say?

830
01:09:30,345 --> 01:09:31,345
I said…

831
01:09:32,504 --> 01:09:34,384
I'm a nice guy, not an asshole.

832
01:09:39,905 --> 01:09:40,985
Anyway, Tofu.

833
01:09:42,025 --> 01:09:45,185
When I was upstairs,
I saw a guy rushing out.

834
01:09:47,345 --> 01:09:48,464
Was it Uncle Saen?

835
01:09:49,664 --> 01:09:52,624
Yes, he saved your mom.

836
01:09:54,105 --> 01:09:55,265
But it's strange.

837
01:09:55,825 --> 01:09:57,265
He seemed to be in a hurry.

838
01:09:57,865 --> 01:10:01,105
It was like he was avoiding someone,
but he was also worried about her.

839
01:10:04,505 --> 01:10:06,704
You haven't had dinner, have you?

840
01:10:07,225 --> 01:10:08,585
Go eat something.

841
01:10:10,465 --> 01:10:11,585
Where are you going?

842
01:10:39,305 --> 01:10:40,465
Hey.

843
01:10:41,465 --> 01:10:43,825
The food is cold. I'll warm it up for you.

844
01:10:43,905 --> 01:10:45,065
I'll help.

845
01:10:55,505 --> 01:10:58,225
Is Nut getting his dad to have dinner?

846
01:11:13,585 --> 01:11:14,865
Take your medicine.

847
01:12:26,185 --> 01:12:28,185
You shouldn't drink so much.

848
01:12:29,265 --> 01:12:30,905
You're not young anymore.

849
01:12:31,465 --> 01:12:32,744
You might fall ill.

850
01:12:34,265 --> 01:12:36,744
Are you worried or are you jinxing me?

851
01:12:38,305 --> 01:12:39,585
Think what you will.

852
01:12:40,145 --> 01:12:43,624
I know. You want me dead, right?
So you can go back to her.

853
01:12:43,704 --> 01:12:46,265
You got back and went straight to her

854
01:12:46,345 --> 01:12:48,744
when your wife was right next door.

855
01:12:49,305 --> 01:12:51,505
Are you that worried about her?

856
01:12:51,585 --> 01:12:52,865
Yes.

857
01:12:53,465 --> 01:12:57,265
I came to see a doctor in Bangkok
because I was worried about her.

858
01:12:57,345 --> 01:12:58,465
Are you happy now?

859
01:13:00,985 --> 01:13:02,145
In that case,

860
01:13:02,225 --> 01:13:03,985
the doctor must have told you

861
01:13:04,065 --> 01:13:06,825
that your little angel has gone insane.

862
01:13:06,905 --> 01:13:08,624
Even if I agreed to a divorce,

863
01:13:08,704 --> 01:13:10,305
you couldn't go back to her,

864
01:13:10,385 --> 01:13:13,505
unless you want a lunatic for a wife.

865
01:13:14,185 --> 01:13:15,784
What difference would it make?

866
01:13:15,865 --> 01:13:18,465
I already have a crazy wife.

867
01:13:19,025 --> 01:13:20,065
Saen!

868
01:13:20,545 --> 01:13:24,065
Go back to her, then.
You've already slept with her.

869
01:13:24,145 --> 01:13:26,345
Are you crazy?

870
01:13:26,425 --> 01:13:28,624
Na and I never did that.

871
01:13:29,704 --> 01:13:30,905
If you didn't,

872
01:13:30,985 --> 01:13:33,545
why did your brother get jealous
and lock you out?

873
01:13:33,624 --> 01:13:36,985
Enough with this love affair nonsense.

874
01:13:37,545 --> 01:13:39,624
Stop being paranoid and open your eyes.

875
01:13:40,105 --> 01:13:43,105
Your nephew is in a coma.
Do you ever think about him?

876
01:13:44,744 --> 01:13:46,345
Why should I?

877
01:13:46,824 --> 01:13:49,545
I didn't put him in a coma.

878
01:13:52,225 --> 01:13:55,385
Even if I do think of him, what can I do?
I'm not a doctor.

879
01:13:55,465 --> 01:13:58,465
And your company is taking care
of his medical bills.

880
01:13:58,945 --> 01:14:00,025
In fact,

881
01:14:00,105 --> 01:14:01,744
he's better off dead.

882
01:14:01,824 --> 01:14:04,945
-Then I'll get the money my dad gave him.
-Jan!

883
01:14:05,664 --> 01:14:08,624
I'll pretend that
this is the drink talking.

884
01:14:08,704 --> 01:14:09,545
I'm not drunk.

885
01:14:09,624 --> 01:14:10,505
I meant what I said

886
01:14:10,585 --> 01:14:12,305
about Tarn and your mistress.

887
01:14:12,385 --> 01:14:15,065
You better show me some respect.

888
01:14:15,145 --> 01:14:16,545
We're not divorced yet.

889
01:14:16,624 --> 01:14:17,744
You're still my husband.

890
01:14:17,824 --> 01:14:19,265
Then give me a damn divorce.

891
01:14:19,345 --> 01:14:22,265
How many times have I sent you
the papers? Just sign them.

892
01:14:22,345 --> 01:14:24,704
No. I won't let you be with her.

893
01:14:31,025 --> 01:14:33,305
You can hold on
to that marriage license, then.

894
01:14:33,985 --> 01:14:36,865
Saen, where are you going? Come back here.

895
01:14:36,945 --> 01:14:38,265
Saen, stop!

896
01:14:38,345 --> 01:14:39,784
-Saen.
-Hey.

897
01:14:40,425 --> 01:14:41,945
You can't leave me like this.

898
01:14:42,425 --> 01:14:44,545
You're drunk. Get back inside.

899
01:14:44,624 --> 01:14:46,905
-Have you no shame?
-No!

900
01:14:47,385 --> 01:14:49,145
You're one to talk.

901
01:14:49,225 --> 01:14:50,744
Do you think I don't know?

902
01:14:50,824 --> 01:14:53,345
You love Nut because he's your son.
Isn't that right?

903
01:14:53,425 --> 01:14:54,865
-Jan!
-Ouch!

904
01:14:57,385 --> 01:14:58,305
Nut.

905
01:15:02,145 --> 01:15:04,744
Where are you staying?
I'll give you a ride.

906
01:15:04,824 --> 01:15:06,545
Saen.

907
01:15:07,025 --> 01:15:08,145
Don't go.

908
01:15:08,704 --> 01:15:10,185
We're done here.

909
01:15:10,744 --> 01:15:12,664
Saen.

910
01:15:12,744 --> 01:15:14,345
Saen, don't go!

911
01:15:14,425 --> 01:15:15,945
Get back here, Saen!

912
01:15:16,025 --> 01:15:17,065
-Come back!
-Stop it!

913
01:15:26,865 --> 01:15:28,105
Saen.

914
01:15:28,664 --> 01:15:29,824
Saen.

915
01:15:29,905 --> 01:15:32,425
Saen!

916
01:15:32,985 --> 01:15:33,985
Nut.

917
01:15:38,545 --> 01:15:41,105
It's late. Where has Nut gone?

918
01:15:42,145 --> 01:15:43,744
I don't know.

919
01:15:48,425 --> 01:15:50,824
I'll go and see if Jan is okay.

920
01:15:56,065 --> 01:15:57,185
Jan.

921
01:15:58,185 --> 01:15:59,265
Mr. Saen.

922
01:15:59,744 --> 01:16:01,185
What's all the commotion about?

923
01:16:01,265 --> 01:16:03,505
Jan is home, but her husband left.

924
01:16:03,985 --> 01:16:06,624
I wasn't prying.

925
01:16:06,704 --> 01:16:08,905
-Hey.
-I just poked my face out and saw her

926
01:16:08,985 --> 01:16:10,585
having a fight with her husband.

927
01:16:10,664 --> 01:16:12,425
Then he left in a car with Nut.

928
01:16:12,985 --> 01:16:14,305
Nut went with Mr. Saen?

929
01:16:14,385 --> 01:16:18,265
That's right. I may be old,
but my eyes are like an eagle's.

930
01:16:19,865 --> 01:16:21,624
Should we go check on Jan?

931
01:16:21,704 --> 01:16:22,865
There's no need for that.

932
01:16:22,945 --> 01:16:26,305
Jan is a strong woman. She's fine.

933
01:16:26,385 --> 01:16:28,105
She probably just threw a tantrum.

934
01:16:28,185 --> 01:16:32,425
Don't be too quick to judge
who's strong or weak.

935
01:16:32,505 --> 01:16:35,585
You're not in their shoes.

936
01:16:35,664 --> 01:16:37,425
So don't judge them, okay?

937
01:16:37,505 --> 01:16:39,065
-Okay.
-All right?

938
01:16:39,145 --> 01:16:42,784
Let's go before they run out
of deep-fried dough sticks and soy milk.

939
01:16:42,865 --> 01:16:45,664
-It's already late. Don't be so nosy.
-Okay.

940
01:16:45,744 --> 01:16:48,025
Stop poking your nose in others' affairs.

941
01:16:48,505 --> 01:16:51,425
-Aren't you sick of soy milk yet?
-Never.

942
01:16:51,505 --> 01:16:53,265
I could have it every day.

943
01:17:14,664 --> 01:17:16,824
I've done so much for you.

944
01:17:18,345 --> 01:17:20,145
Are you really going to leave me?

945
01:17:57,664 --> 01:17:58,824
Thank you, Nut.

946
01:18:00,945 --> 01:18:01,985
It's fine.

947
01:18:04,425 --> 01:18:07,865
I barged into your house today.

948
01:18:07,945 --> 01:18:09,185
I'm sorry about that.

949
01:18:09,265 --> 01:18:10,585
You don't have to be sorry.

950
01:18:11,465 --> 01:18:13,945
You should visit us sometime.

951
01:18:14,704 --> 01:18:16,185
We're family after all.

952
01:18:17,704 --> 01:18:19,385
And my dad is already gone.

953
01:18:35,145 --> 01:18:36,305
I forgot.

954
01:18:38,545 --> 01:18:40,065
Jan doesn't want you to see us.

955
01:18:41,985 --> 01:18:44,385
I don't care what she thinks.

956
01:18:44,465 --> 01:18:46,945
She's mistaken
and she has the wrong idea about things.

957
01:18:47,585 --> 01:18:50,025
But I don't want her
to pick a fight with your mom.

958
01:18:51,065 --> 01:18:52,505
Your mom is a poor soul.

959
01:18:53,025 --> 01:18:55,265
I don't want to cause her
any more trouble.

960
01:19:03,305 --> 01:19:04,784
How is she doing?

961
01:19:33,025 --> 01:19:34,025
Uncle Saen.

962
01:19:36,225 --> 01:19:37,065
Hello.

963
01:19:40,704 --> 01:19:43,025
How's your mom? Is she doing okay?

964
01:19:43,585 --> 01:19:44,585
She's fine.

965
01:19:44,664 --> 01:19:46,985
Do you want to come inside?
Dad is also home.

966
01:19:48,425 --> 01:19:49,985
I've got an errand to run.

967
01:19:52,065 --> 01:19:54,185
-Can you give this to your mom?
-Sure.

968
01:19:54,824 --> 01:19:55,824
Thank you.

969
01:19:58,784 --> 01:20:00,145
Take good care of your mom.

970
01:20:01,945 --> 01:20:02,985
I will.

971
01:20:12,865 --> 01:20:13,865
Who was it?

972
01:20:13,945 --> 01:20:15,145
It was Uncle Saen.

973
01:20:16,664 --> 01:20:18,345
Here's a gift from Chiang Mai.

974
01:20:25,305 --> 01:20:27,664
Do not accept anything
from Saen from now on.

975
01:20:39,905 --> 01:20:41,664
Why did Dad do that, Mom?

976
01:20:42,385 --> 01:20:44,265
Uncle Saen is his brother.

977
01:21:00,905 --> 01:21:03,025
You ask the same question
every time we meet.

978
01:21:07,305 --> 01:21:08,664
You've seen how she is.

979
01:21:09,865 --> 01:21:12,385
I asked Tofu to help look after her,

980
01:21:13,025 --> 01:21:15,465
but he had gone out
when she fell off the ladder.

981
01:21:17,305 --> 01:21:18,824
Thank God you got there in time.

982
01:21:20,664 --> 01:21:22,225
Is that kid a houseboy?

983
01:21:24,585 --> 01:21:27,185
He's a friend of mine, not a houseboy.

984
01:21:28,065 --> 01:21:29,545
He's a little bit goofy.

985
01:21:30,704 --> 01:21:33,905
Don't mind him if he does anything weird.

986
01:21:36,185 --> 01:21:37,704
From what I've seen,

987
01:21:37,784 --> 01:21:41,025
he seems like an innocent,
trustworthy kid.

988
01:21:42,265 --> 01:21:43,545
You work hard.

989
01:21:43,624 --> 01:21:45,824
It's good he's helping you
look after your mom.

990
01:21:53,505 --> 01:21:55,225
It would've been nice

991
01:21:56,105 --> 01:21:57,624
if she had married you.

992
01:22:00,624 --> 01:22:02,345
She would have you to care for her.

993
01:22:05,624 --> 01:22:07,945
If I had a loving father like you,

994
01:22:10,865 --> 01:22:12,905
my mom and I wouldn't have
ended up like this.

995
01:22:19,265 --> 01:22:20,905
If we could see the future,

996
01:22:22,624 --> 01:22:24,905
no one would ever make a mistake.

997
01:22:28,305 --> 01:22:30,585
But once you make a mistake,

998
01:22:32,545 --> 01:22:34,265
you're bound to do it again.

999
01:22:53,945 --> 01:22:56,425
I'm home, Dad.

1000
01:22:56,505 --> 01:22:57,945
You were gone a long time.

1001
01:22:58,425 --> 01:23:01,105
I stopped by a popular porridge stall
and got you some.

1002
01:23:01,664 --> 01:23:03,425
It's near Tofu's house.

1003
01:23:03,985 --> 01:23:06,585
The queue was so long I almost gave up.

1004
01:23:08,065 --> 01:23:09,145
Thank you, son.

1005
01:23:10,425 --> 01:23:11,784
You're welcome.

1006
01:23:11,865 --> 01:23:13,704
You're not home very often.

1007
01:23:14,985 --> 01:23:18,065
I just wanted you to have a good meal.

1008
01:23:20,305 --> 01:23:22,624
I wasn't thanking you for the porridge.

1009
01:23:23,345 --> 01:23:24,784
I meant Tofu.

1010
01:23:29,225 --> 01:23:32,225
Thank you for introducing him to me.

1011
01:23:33,425 --> 01:23:35,824
I know you did it because I miss Neung.

1012
01:23:50,265 --> 01:23:51,265
Hey, Dad.

1013
01:23:51,905 --> 01:23:53,465
Let me ask you something.

1014
01:23:54,225 --> 01:23:55,225
What is it?

1015
01:23:55,305 --> 01:23:58,345
Did you have a lovechild
with a secret mistress?

1016
01:23:58,425 --> 01:24:01,145
You little devil. Watch your mouth.

1017
01:24:01,225 --> 01:24:04,065
Look at me. I'm working my ass off.

1018
01:24:04,545 --> 01:24:06,185
Would I have time for a mistress?

1019
01:24:06,265 --> 01:24:07,624
It's strange.

1020
01:24:07,704 --> 01:24:09,505
Tofu looks exactly like Neung.

1021
01:24:10,305 --> 01:24:11,305
Wait a second.

1022
01:24:11,824 --> 01:24:13,385
Maybe Neung has been reincarnated.

1023
01:24:14,265 --> 01:24:17,345
Dad. You watch too much TV.

1024
01:24:17,425 --> 01:24:19,905
Neung has only been dead for ten years.

1025
01:24:19,985 --> 01:24:23,025
There's no way he could be reincarnated
as someone my age.

1026
01:24:23,585 --> 01:24:25,624
That's true.

1027
01:24:27,624 --> 01:24:28,624
Hey, Dad.

1028
01:24:29,545 --> 01:24:33,065
Why don't you do some digging into Tofu?

1029
01:24:34,905 --> 01:24:39,105
Do you think I have time for that?

1030
01:24:39,905 --> 01:24:41,465
Please, Dad.

1031
01:24:41,545 --> 01:24:44,545
Aren't you a tiny bit curious?

1032
01:24:47,105 --> 01:24:48,345
I'll look into it.

1033
01:24:48,945 --> 01:24:51,704
Enough chit-chat. Eat up.

1034
01:24:53,385 --> 01:24:54,385
Here.

1035
01:24:55,704 --> 01:24:56,905
-Take a spoon.
-Thank you.

1036
01:24:57,624 --> 01:24:58,824
I got it.

1037
01:24:58,905 --> 01:25:00,345
Eat up. Don't wait for me.

1038
01:25:16,025 --> 01:25:18,585
The ones who love each other
aren't together.

1039
01:25:18,664 --> 01:25:21,305
And the ones who are together
don't love each other.

1040
01:25:27,025 --> 01:25:28,624
Who do you mean, Ms. Left Slipper?

1041
01:25:29,105 --> 01:25:30,865
You've been a human for ages,

1042
01:25:30,945 --> 01:25:32,945
but you're just as dumb as before.

1043
01:25:33,025 --> 01:25:35,225
Why do you have to be mean to Tofu?

1044
01:25:35,305 --> 01:25:38,225
Are you jealous that he got to be human?

1045
01:25:38,305 --> 01:25:41,985
Why would I be jealous of a teddy bear
who lives a pathetic life

1046
01:25:42,065 --> 01:25:46,265
without any vision, ideology,
nor the spirit of a free man.

1047
01:25:46,345 --> 01:25:48,345
That's enough.

1048
01:25:48,425 --> 01:25:50,385
What I just said…

1049
01:25:50,465 --> 01:25:54,985
I was talking about Mrs. Na, Mr. Saen,

1050
01:25:55,065 --> 01:25:57,265
and Jan.

1051
01:25:58,585 --> 01:26:00,784
Do you mean Mr. Saen loves Mrs. Na,

1052
01:26:01,345 --> 01:26:02,865
but he can't be with her?

1053
01:26:04,225 --> 01:26:06,305
Does that mean he doesn't love Jan?

1054
01:26:08,305 --> 01:26:10,624
You've been married to Mr. Saen
for a long time.

1055
01:26:11,425 --> 01:26:13,704
How come I've never seen him here?

1056
01:26:16,345 --> 01:26:18,985
My husband works in Chiang Mai.

1057
01:26:19,065 --> 01:26:21,225
He rarely flies back home.

1058
01:26:21,305 --> 01:26:23,744
But I fly over there quite often.

1059
01:26:25,425 --> 01:26:29,105
You must be lonely
since you rarely get to see him.

1060
01:26:30,425 --> 01:26:32,345
Why don't you move to Chiang Mai with him?

1061
01:26:33,585 --> 01:26:36,985
Well, I guess it's my bad luck.

1062
01:26:37,065 --> 01:26:40,345
Soon after we got married,
our company started failing.

1063
01:26:40,425 --> 01:26:43,985
My dad had to let other investors
help run the company.

1064
01:26:44,065 --> 01:26:46,824
Saen took responsibility by quitting

1065
01:26:46,905 --> 01:26:48,704
and he got a new job in Chiang Mai

1066
01:26:49,265 --> 01:26:51,505
even though it wasn't his fault.

1067
01:26:51,985 --> 01:26:53,784
The economy was just bad.

1068
01:26:54,664 --> 01:26:58,585
In the end, we couldn't hold on
and we had to sell our factory.

1069
01:26:59,624 --> 01:27:03,824
I heard Sibmeun had invested his money
in a house in this neighborhood.

1070
01:27:03,905 --> 01:27:06,425
It was in a good spot
and the price was reasonable,

1071
01:27:06,505 --> 01:27:08,225
so I bought one for myself.

1072
01:27:09,505 --> 01:27:12,624
I spent all my savings on this house.

1073
01:27:12,704 --> 01:27:14,905
How can I leave it?

1074
01:27:16,385 --> 01:27:18,864
I never thought that one day,

1075
01:27:18,945 --> 01:27:22,345
Nut would move in next door with his mom.

1076
01:27:25,465 --> 01:27:29,385
Actually, I feel just as sorry for Jan
as I do for Mrs. Na.

1077
01:27:33,305 --> 01:27:36,824
There must be something else
between Mrs. Na, Mr. Saen, and Jan

1078
01:27:37,345 --> 01:27:39,505
that I don't know about.

1079
01:27:39,585 --> 01:27:42,505
But it goes to show
that everyone has problems to deal with.

1080
01:27:43,265 --> 01:27:45,185
And their problems

1081
01:27:45,265 --> 01:27:48,624
are way too complicated for me
to understand in such a short time.

1082
01:27:56,505 --> 01:27:58,905
About life in high school?

1083
01:27:58,985 --> 01:28:00,744
And it's not an odd thing anymore.

1084
01:28:00,824 --> 01:28:02,864
But it's still not normal.

1085
01:28:02,945 --> 01:28:05,905
If for you, normal means
only thinking the way you do,

1086
01:28:05,985 --> 01:28:07,744
then half the world would be abnormal.

1087
01:28:07,824 --> 01:28:11,345
That plot of land and your house
should have gone to me,

1088
01:28:11,425 --> 01:28:14,505
not a brat like you who has never
contributed to the family business.

1089
01:28:14,585 --> 01:28:15,744
If you want it,

1090
01:28:16,265 --> 01:28:17,664
wait until I'm dead.

1091
01:28:17,744 --> 01:28:18,744
Tofu!

1092
01:28:21,664 --> 01:28:23,385
Where did you get a key to my room?

1093
01:28:23,465 --> 01:28:24,545
Well…

1094
01:28:24,624 --> 01:28:27,145
Well, the best way
to get over your old love

1095
01:28:27,225 --> 01:28:29,025
is to find a new one, right?

1096
01:28:30,385 --> 01:28:31,704
If you're happy,

1097
01:28:32,185 --> 01:28:34,864
those romantic scenes
you're struggling with

1098
01:28:35,385 --> 01:28:36,704
will come to you naturally.

1099
01:28:36,784 --> 01:28:39,225
Shall I find someone for you?
They're crazy about you.

1100
01:28:39,305 --> 01:28:40,505
It's either Prib or Tofu.

